               <msContents>
                  <summary>Declaration of property from Panopolis (modern name: Akhmim), Egypt, written on papyrus. Declaration lists small holdings in various numbered plots in the Panopolite Nome including the Upper toparchy. Types of land include sown and dry land. Mentions the surveyors Marcus and Zoilos. Part of the archive of Ammon, the well-known scholastikos, or lawyer</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Dimensions of fragments are 21.2 x 20.5 cm. or smaller</note>
                     <note type="general">34 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the recto in two columns</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 1.5 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 183 was formerly P.Duk.inv. G 183</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
